data.title: Burundi 10,000 Francs Banknote, 2022, P-59, UNC
meta_keywords: President Melchior Ndadaye banknote from Burundi
data.meta_description: This uncirculated 10,000 Burundian franc note is a standard circulation banknote issued by the Bank of the Republic of Burundi. It is a red note that is dated 07 November 2022, bear the signatures of Dieudonne Murengerantwari and Desire Musharitse, and measures 145 mm x 72 mm. Its obverse side features a hippopotamus, the coat of arms of Burundi, and the portraits of Prince Rwagasore and President Melchior Ndadaye. Its reverse side shows an outline map of Burundi and plants. Security features include a windowed security thread with bank monogram and a cow head, a fish-shaped see through feature, and a watermark of Louis Rwagasore with an electrotype bank logo.
